dcterms:description: This dataset represents defendants who were released on bail at the U.S. state courts during 1990-2009. Nodes represent clients within a bail bank, features are gender, loan amount, and other account-related details. The objective is to categorize clients' credit risk as either high or low, with 'gender' designated as the sensitive feature.
dcterms:title: Bail

dcterms:description: Extracted from the Adult Data Set. Nodes represent defendants released in Germany from 1990 to 2009, connected by edges based on shared past criminal records and demographics. The goal is predicting a defendant's likelihood of committing either a violent or nonviolent crime post-release, with 'race' as the sensitive feature.
dcterms:title: German
